article.headline: Yale 86, Harvard 71
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Sophomore forward Ross Morin scored a career-high 19 points to lead Yale to a 86-71 win over Harvard in the Ivy League on Saturday. Sophomore forward Travis Pinick added a career-high 16 points while junior guard Eric Flato had 14 points for the Bulldogs (12-11, 8-2). Yale, which has won 12 of 14 overall against the Crimson, shot 62.7 from the field in the game. The Bulldogs remained a half-game behind first-place Penn in the Ivy standings. Brad Unger and Drew Housman scored 16 points each for Harvard (10-14, 3-7), which lost its fourth straight game. Yale scored the game's first nine points and shot 59.3 percent from the field in the first half, but Harvard trailed by just two at the half (38-36) thanks to its dominance on the glass. The Crimson out-rebounded the Bulldogs 20-8 in the half, including an 11-2 advantage on the offensive boards.
